    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <comment>As a consequence of warming wet loose snow avalanches are possible. &lt;br/> The wind slabs can be released easily in some places in particular on steep shady slopes. Weak layers in the old snowpack necessitate caution and restraint.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>&lt;br/> The spring-like weather conditions will give rise to unfavourable bonding of the snowpack in some cases on very steep sunny slopes. As a consequence of highly fluctuating temperatures and solar radiation a treacherous avalanche situation will develop. These conditions will cause a weakening of the snowpack in gullies and bowls and behind abrupt changes in terrain. This applies in particular on steep south, southwest and west facing slopes above the tree line.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
